Details.Education:
Per the Office of Personnel Management Qualifications Standards, education may be substituted for experience at the GS-11 grade level as follows: Successful completion of a Ph.D. or equivalent doctoral degree;
or
Successful completion of three full years of progressively higher level graduate education leading to a Ph.D. or equivalent degree;
or
Successful completion of an LL.M. degree that is related to the position being filled. https://www.usajobs.gov/Help/working-in-government/unique-hiringpaths/students/federal-occupations-by-college-major/;
or
A combination of experience and graduate education as described above that equates to one year of experience. The percentage of required education plus the percentage of required experience must equal one hundred percent.

MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-09 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector performing Human Resources work under close supervision of supervisor or Senior HR Specialist that involves providing advice and assistance to employees and managers, program administration, research, and case management in matters related to conduct, performance, attendance, dispute resolution, and providing guidance and consultation to management on a variety of labor relations matters. Specialized experience must demonstrate performing the following duties: 1) Applying Human resources (HR) principles, concept and practices to provide advice and guidance to management on employee and labor relations issues;
2) Using statutes, rules, regulations and case law to devise case strategy in precedential situations;
3) Work with supervisor or Senior HR Specialist to recommending courses of action that meet organizational needs and are in compliance with controlling status, regulations, policies and labor relation contract requirements. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series
